<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="210" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1452,2017]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1452,1477]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. F 
<number box="[306,316,1452,1476]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="1.0">1</number>
with basiventral denticle, with adjacent basal spines stronger (
<figureCitation box="[1076,1151,1452,1477]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,193,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1435,193,1900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Hemerodromia amazonensis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 1. habitus, lateral view; 2. fore femur and tibia; 3. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia; 4. terminalia, lateral view; 5. cercus, dorsal view; 6. subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 7. phallus, lateral view; 8. hypandrium, epandrium and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252069/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="210">
Fig. 
<number box="[1135,1151,1452,1476]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
); epandrium fused with hypandrium (
<figureCitation box="[301,370,1487,1512]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,193,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1435,193,1900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Hemerodromia amazonensis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 1. habitus, lateral view; 2. fore femur and tibia; 3. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia; 4. terminalia, lateral view; 5. cercus, dorsal view; 6. subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 7. phallus, lateral view; 8. hypandrium, epandrium and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252069/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="210">
Fig. 
<number box="[354,370,1488,1512]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
); surstylus complex, subovate lobe with spine-like setae at tip on inner face (
<figureCitation box="[1233,1302,1487,1512]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,193,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1435,193,1900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Hemerodromia amazonensis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 1. habitus, lateral view; 2. fore femur and tibia; 3. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia; 4. terminalia, lateral view; 5. cercus, dorsal view; 6. subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 7. phallus, lateral view; 8. hypandrium, epandrium and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252069/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="210">
Fig. 
<number box="[1286,1302,1487,1512]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="212" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1452,2017]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,412,1524,1549]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210">Description. Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[426,491,1524,1549]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,193,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1435,193,1900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Hemerodromia amazonensis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 1. habitus, lateral view; 2. fore femur and tibia; 3. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia; 4. terminalia, lateral view; 5. cercus, dorsal view; 6. subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 7. phallus, lateral view; 8. hypandrium, epandrium and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252069/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="210">
Fig. 
<number box="[478,491,1524,1548]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[515,579,1524,1549]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210">Head</emphasis>
. Dark brown to black, antenna and mouthparts yellow with all setae whitish; ocellar triangle with 
<number box="[402,416,1560,1584]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="1.0">1</number>
pair of proclinate setae; anterior ocellus larger. Eyes iridescent black, very narrowly separated on face bearing fine reclinate setulae. Frons with 
<number box="[810,824,1596,1620]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="3.0">3</number>
setulae; small vertical setae contiguous with uniseriate postocular setae. Occiput bearing scattered fine hairs. Clypeus with rather dense short downwardly directed pile. Proboscis slightly curved, with setae yellow. Antenna with scape and pedicel bearing distinct short dorsal setulae; postpedicel about 
<number box="[358,392,1703,1728]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="1.5">1.5</number>
X as long as wide, stylus ~ 
<number box="[711,746,1704,1728]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="0.8">0.8</number>
X as long as postpedicel. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1039,1128,1703,1728]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1144,1211,1703,1728]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,193,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1435,193,1900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Hemerodromia amazonensis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 1. habitus, lateral view; 2. fore femur and tibia; 3. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia; 4. terminalia, lateral view; 5. cercus, dorsal view; 6. subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 7. phallus, lateral view; 8. hypandrium, epandrium and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252069/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="210">
Fig. 
<number box="[1198,1211,1704,1728]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Elongate, slightly arched ventrally, dorsum yellow except brownish on prothoracic collar, narrowly behind postpronotal lobe, suture between katepisternum and meron; antepronotum with anterior margin almost straight; scutum with yellow setae, very small and fine except one notopleural. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[642,698,1812,1837]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210">Legs</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[713,778,1812,1837]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,193,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1435,193,1900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Hemerodromia amazonensis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 1. habitus, lateral view; 2. fore femur and tibia; 3. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia; 4. terminalia, lateral view; 5. cercus, dorsal view; 6. subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 7. phallus, lateral view; 8. hypandrium, epandrium and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252069/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="210">
Fig. 
<number box="[765,778,1812,1836]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Whitish yellow. C 
<number box="[1009,1019,1812,1836]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="1.0">1</number>
~ 
<number box="[1048,1082,1812,1836]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="1.4">1.4</number>
X longer than distance between C 
<number box="[173,183,1848,1872]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="1.0">1</number>
and C2, 
<date box="[290,324,1847,1872]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210">6X</date>
as long as wide with some pale dorsoapical setae. F 
<number box="[930,940,1848,1872]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="1.0">1</number>
~ 
<number box="[974,1007,1848,1872]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="1.1">1.1</number>
X as long as C 
<number box="[1184,1195,1848,1872]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="1.0">1</number>
, 
<number box="[1209,1243,1847,1872]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="3.5">3.5</number>
–4.0X as long as wide; femoral formula 
<date box="[415,487,1884,1909]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="1923-07-01">
<number box="[415,429,1884,1909]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="7.0">7</number>
/ 
<number box="[438,467,1884,1909]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="23.0">23</number>
/ 
<number box="[478,487,1884,1909]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="1.0">1</number>
</date>
+ 
<number box="[503,531,1884,1909]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="21.0">21</number>
/ 
<number box="[541,554,1884,1909]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="5.0">5</number>
, basal spines stronger (
<figureCitation box="[821,891,1884,1909]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,193,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1435,193,1900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Hemerodromia amazonensis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 1. habitus, lateral view; 2. fore femur and tibia; 3. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia; 4. terminalia, lateral view; 5. cercus, dorsal view; 6. subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 7. phallus, lateral view; 8. hypandrium, epandrium and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252069/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="210">
Fig. 
<number box="[875,891,1884,1908]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
); denticles confined to distal 
<number box="[1230,1267,1884,1908]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="0.7">0.7</number>
, 
<number box="[1280,1294,1884,1908]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="2.0">2</number>
rows linear, black, without distal discontinuity, converging distally but divergent at tip. T 
<number box="[1011,1021,1920,1944]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="1.0">1</number>
~ 
<number box="[1050,1085,1920,1944]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="0.8">0.8</number>
X as long as F 
<number box="[1249,1260,1920,1944]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="1.0">1</number>
, evenly curved, ventral face shallowly concave; with 
<number box="[578,592,1956,1980]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="2.0">2</number>
rows of 
<number box="[697,766,1956,1980]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="19.0" valueMax="21.0" valueMin="17.0">17–21</number>
sharply pointed spinose setae ventrally; dorsal ciliation of decumbent short pale setulae, denser distally; with small apicoventral extension on T 
<number box="[1106,1116,1992,2016]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="1.0">1</number>
bearing strong apical spine.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252069/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="211" targetBox="[152,1434,193,1894]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1921,2004]" pageId="2" pageNumber="211">
